The current Georgia Teacher of the Year/my fellow FVSU wildcat/my friend Casey M. Bethel visited Newton County Schools to speak with the Leadership Team.  He delivered an awesome message that constantly reminds me of how proud I am of him! 
There's a story behind this picture and why we posed like this for it..............Nikkita Davenport Warfield, Casey, and I all started at FVSU in 1996 and graduated together in 2000.  Ironically, we were 3 of 6 on FVSUs 1999-2000 Royal Court (homecoming court). We were leaders back then and we continue to be leaders in our own way now! 
This picture is a testament not only to the fact that HBCUs train dynamic leaders, but also how HBCUs are great post secondary institutions! The experience that I gained from my HBCU went beyond a quality education as I had valuable life experiences that taught me lessons too.  Fort Valley State University taught me advocacy, patience, humility, and to be strong in my faith. 
I'm grateful that FVSU believed in me and gave me an academic scholarship many moons ago because it afforded me the opportunity to meet and surround myself with dynamic people like these two!!!! #fvsuproud #fvsu #fortvalleystateuniversity #fvsuwildcats #leaders #innateleadership #boardmember #districtdirector #georgiateacheroftheyear #principal #director
